data.meta_description: Zhejiangosaurus is an extinct genus of ankylosaurian dinosaur from the Upper Cretaceous of Zhejiang, eastern China. It was first named by a group of Chinese authors LÃ¼ Junchang, Jin Xingsheng, Sheng Yiming and Li Yihong in 2007 and the type species is Zhejiangosaurus lishuiensis. It has no diagnostic features, and thus is a nomen dubium.
